simulator.payloads

  • Packages that use simulator.payloads 
    Package Description
    simulator.elevatorcontrol
    Contains classes that manipulate the simulated environmental objects.
    simulator.elevatormodules
    Provides sensors for detecting car position, door position, and door reversal triggers, and actuators for turning on button lights moving the doors.
    simulator.framework
    Provides the core infrastructure for simulating the network and elevator.
    simulator.framework.faultmodels  
    simulator.framework.faults  
    simulator.payloads
    The message types that can be sent on the simulated network.
    simulator.payloads.translators
    The abstract CanPayload translator and some basic translators.

  • Classes in simulator.payloads used by simulator.payloads 
    Class and Description
    AtFloorPayload
    Indicates True when the Car is above, below, or at Floor[f,b] but close enough that the Car should be traveling at slow speed to be able to stop level with Floor[f,b].
    AtFloorPayload.ReadableAtFloorPayload 
    AtFloorPayload.WriteableAtFloorPayload 
    CanMailbox
    CanMailbox is the Payload object that is used by the elevator.framework.CANNetwork.
    CanMailbox.ReadableCanMailbox 
    CanMailbox.WriteableCanMailbox 
    CANNetwork.CanConnection
    This connector only allows time-triggered connections to the CAN network.
    CarCallPayload
    Network messages indicate whether a car call has been requested for Hallway[f,b], and framework messages indicate whether the button is currently held down.
    CarCallPayload.ReadableCarCallPayload 
    CarCallPayload.WriteableCarCallPayload 
    CarLanternPayload
    Indicates whether the Up/Down arrows placed on the car doorframes are illuminated.
    CarLanternPayload.ReadableCarLanternPayload 
    CarLanternPayload.WriteableCarLanternPayload 
    CarLevelPositionPayload.ReadableCarLevelPositionPayload 
    CarLevelPositionPayload.WriteableCarLevelPositionPayload 
    CarLightPayload
    Framework message sent by a controller is a command to the light actuator to turn the light on or off; framework message from the light indicates whether the light is on or off.
    CarLightPayload.ReadableCarLightPayload 
    CarLightPayload.WriteableCarLightPayload 
    CarPositionIndicatorPayload
    Framework message is a command to the Car Position Indicator to display the specified floor number to the Passengers in the Car.
    CarPositionIndicatorPayload.ReadableCarPositionIndicatorPayload 
    CarPositionIndicatorPayload.WriteableCarPositionIndicatorPayload 
    CarPositionPayload.ReadableCarPositionPayload 
    CarPositionPayload.WriteableCarPositionPayload 
    CarWeightAlarmPayload
    Network message indicates whether the alarm inside the car is ringing; framework message is a command for the Car Weight Alarm to turn on or off.
    CarWeightAlarmPayload.ReadableCarWeightAlarmPayload 
    CarWeightAlarmPayload.WriteableCarWeightAlarmPayload 
    CarWeightPayload
    Network message indicates the observed weight (in tenths of pounds) of all Passengers in the Car according to the Car Weight Sensor.
    CarWeightPayload.ReadableCarWeightPayload 
    CarWeightPayload.WriteableCarWeightPayload 
    DoorClosedPayload
    Indicates whether a door is fully closed.
    DoorClosedPayload.ReadableDoorClosedPayload 
    DoorClosedPayload.WriteableDoorClosedPayload 
    DoorMotorPayload
    Framework message that commands the doors to open, close, nudge, or stop moving.
    DoorMotorPayload.ReadableDoorMotorPayload 
    DoorMotorPayload.WriteableDoorMotorPayload 
    DoorOpenPayload
    Indicates whether a door is fully open.
    DoorOpenPayload.ReadableDoorOpenPayload 
    DoorOpenPayload.WriteableDoorOpenPayload 
    DoorPositionPayload
    Internal framework message indicates how far open a door is.
    DoorPositionPayload.ReadableDoorPositionPayload 
    DoorPositionPayload.WriteableDoorPositionPayload 
    DoorReversalPayload
    Framework message indicates whether a door reversal switch has been triggered.
    DoorReversalPayload.ReadableDoorReversalPayload 
    DoorReversalPayload.WriteableDoorReversalPayload 
    DrivePayload.ReadableDrivePayload 
    DrivePayload.WriteableDrivePayload 
    DriveSpeedPayload.ReadableDriveSpeedPayload 
    DriveSpeedPayload.WriteableDriveSpeedPayload 
    EmergencyBrakePayload
    Supplies emergency braking in case of safety violation such as hoistway limit over-run or movement with doors open.
    EmergencyBrakePayload.ReadableEmergencyBrakePayload 
    EmergencyBrakePayload.WriteableEmergencyBrakePayload 
    FaultPayload
    No Fault payloads are currently implemented, but if you wanted to fault specific objects, you can create a new payload class that descends from this class and use simulator.faults.FaultPayloadFault to inject it at certain times using the -ff file.
    HallCallPayload
    Network message indicates whether a hall call has been requested at Hallway[f,b] for direction d, and a framework message indicates whether the button is currently held down.
    HallCallPayload.ReadableHallCallPayload 
    HallCallPayload.WriteableHallCallPayload 
    HallLightPayload
    Framework message sent by a controller is a command to the light actuator to turn the light on or off; framework message from the light indicates whether the light is on or off.
    HallLightPayload.ReadableHallLightPayload 
    HallLightPayload.WriteableHallLightPayload 
    HoistwayLimitPayload
    A HoistwayLimit[d] switch activates when the car has over-run the hoistway limits and is in an emergency stopping situation.
    HoistwayLimitPayload.ReadableHoistwayLimitPayload 
    HoistwayLimitPayload.WriteableHoistwayLimitPayload 
    InternalPayload
    Tag interface that prevents controller objects from accessing payloads that are used internally by the simulator.
    LevelingPayload
    Indicates True when the Car is above, below, or at Floor[f,b] but close enough that the Car should be traveling at slow speed to be able to stop level with Floor[f,b].
    LevelingPayload.ReadableLevelingPayload 
    LevelingPayload.WriteableLevelingPayload 
    Networkable
    An adaptor for receiving event triggered messages.
    NetworkConnection 
    NetworkScheduler
    A generic computer network that transmits "high priority" messages before "low priority" messages.
    NetworkScheduler.Connection
    Allows elevator components to send and receive messages through the network.
    NetworkUtilization
    Utility class for keeping track of the the amount of time the network is used vs.
    Payload
    A message sent between components in the elevator.
    PersonWeightPayload
    Indicates that a Passenger of a particular mass has entered or exited the car.
    PersonWeightPayload.ReadablePersonWeightPayload 
    PersonWeightPayload.WriteablePersonWeightPayload 
    PhysicalNetwork
    Implement physical state representation of the system as a message passing network.
    PhysicalNetwork.PhysicalConnection
    Connects elevator components to the physical framework.
    PhysicalPayload

    PhysicalPayload.PhysicalReadablePayload 
    PhysicalPayload.PhysicalWriteablePayload
